{{Infobox language |name=Adjukru |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |speakers=100,000 |date=1999 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Kwa languages|Kwa]] |iso3=adj |glotto=adio1239 |glottorefname=Adioukrou }}
'''Adjukru''' (Adioukrou, Adyoukrou, Adyukru, Ajukru) is a language of uncertain classification within the [[Kwa language|Kwa]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] family. It is spoken in [[Ivory Coast]] by the [[Adjoukrou people]].
